Package InfrastructureManager.Modules.Scenario

Class Scenario

java.lang.Object
InfrastructureManager.PlatformObject
InfrastructureManager.Modules.Scenario.ScenarioModuleObject
InfrastructureManager.Modules.Scenario.Scenario
All Implemented Interfaces:
PlatformInput
public class Scenario
extends ScenarioModuleObject
implements PlatformInput
Class representing an scenario, defined as a series of events that happen with a defined and guaranteed timing.

This class is a form of Platform input, in the sense that gives the different commands for the platform to read and process with the defined timing.

  • Method Details

    • read

      public java.lang.String read() throws java.lang.InterruptedException
      Implementation of the PlatformInput interface. It controls the execution of the different events in the scenario and returns the different corresponding commands.

      In other words, it returns the command of an event, blocks for the defined time for the next event and then returns the other command (This with all events in the scenario).

      This blocks until the scenario is started.

      Specified by:
      read in interface PlatformInput
      Returns:
      Command of the current event in the scenario. Returns null when an error occurs or when the scenario is finished
      Throws:
      java.lang.InterruptedException - If interrupted while waiting on an event.
